From: Daniel Serpell <daniel@serpell.net>
Date: Fri, 6 Mar 2026 20:56:48 -0300
Subject: [PATCH] Fix build with Boost 1.89+

Newer Boost releases removed the Boost.System library. Boost.System has
been header-only since Boost 1.69, so PulseView does not need to request
the removed system component.

---
 CMakeLists.txt | 2 +-
 1 file changed, 1 insertion(+), 1 deletion(-)

diff --git a/CMakeLists.txt b/CMakeLists.txt
index 707441dd..c37e0810 100644
--- a/CMakeLists.txt
+++ b/CMakeLists.txt
@@ -125,7 +125,7 @@ endif()
 
 set(QT_LIBRARIES Qt5::Gui Qt5::Widgets Qt5::Svg)
 
-set(BOOSTCOMPS filesystem serialization system)
+set(BOOSTCOMPS filesystem serialization)
 if(ENABLE_TESTS)
 	list(APPEND BOOSTCOMPS unit_test_framework)
 endif()
